						<div class="postbody">Yeah, PAL vblank is so long that reading the controllers during that time shouldn't make any difference... Just take care of the sprite DMA and controller reading right away, while on NTSC you'd do both these things last, with the controller part possibly spilling into the visible frame.</div>

